            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt and mix",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Line a 30 × 20 cm tin with baking paper. Melt the {{dark-chocolate}}, {{unsalted-butter}}, and {{golden-syrup}} together in a saucepan over very low heat, stirring until smooth. Remove from the heat and leave to cool for 3 to 4 minutes. It should be fluid but no longer steaming. Add the {{digestive-biscuit}} pieces, {{marshmallows}}, {{glace-cherries}}, and {{walnuts}} if using, and fold until everything is coated.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Set and cut",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour into the prepared tin and press down gently so the surface is rough and uneven. Dust with {{cocoa-powder}} if using. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours until fully set. Lift out on the paper, transfer to a board, and cut into squares with a sharp knife. Keep refrigerated.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
